  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: In chat screen: to see more messages user taps on chat screen but keyboard is not hidden. We need to hide opened keyboard when user taps on chat.\r\n![chat](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/25224369/7e499ddc-25be-11e7-98d4-2a4fa04ec671.png)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\n- User taps on chat empty space -> keyboard is hidden. \r\n- User taps on input field -> keyboard is shown\r\n- User taps on commands -> relevant keyboard (text or numeric) is shown\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\n- User taps on chat -> keyboard is not hidden and takes half of the screen\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\nvideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7ZjFMeTF6SjhwM1E\r\n- Open Status \r\n- Open 1-1 chat\r\n- Tap on input field -> keyboard is shown\r\n- Tap on chat (I expect that keyboard will be hidden, so there is more space to read)\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.7d67\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n",
